rComments: I had Jasmina for  the kind of teacher you don't like to disappoint. She's very supportive and helpful for those who are struggling. She explains concepts well and makes it clear she considers your education important. She's usually pretty happy and upbeat. Loved taking her class.

Jasmina is a very thoughtful teacher, she makes learning fun and I was really sad when I ended up having a different Russian teacher for my other sections. I hope she gets hired on as  faculty because I think she has a real passion for teaching and she is an amazing person. By the way, her favorite Russian word is "pilasos", giggles will ensue.
